<br>
A fellow wizard and guildmate of mine recently asked me<br>
a question which I cannot answer so I thought I'd post<br>
here and see if anyone has had a similar experience.<br>
<br>
He is Level 51, we play on the Tribunal and recently (since<br>
the last patch) he's been having difficulty casting his L49<br>
Lesser Familiar spell. Specifically he's noticing a significantly<br>
increased fizzle rate.. as in it's usually taking 2 full pools of<br>
mana before he can get a successful conjuration. (as per<br>
his tests). Understandably, his Conjuration skill is in the<br>
mid 90s, but it's been that level all along and only recently<br>
has there been a serious increase in fizzles. I attempted<br>
to reproduce this with my 56 wiz who's conj is 198 but<br>
did not see the same problem.. (probably due to my high<br>
Conj skill)<br>
<br>
.. so my questions are: a) were there recent changes to the<br>
sensitivity of conjuration skill level when casting and/or b) <br>
has anyone else noticed this same thing?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your time &amp; I'd appreciate any<br>
insight you might have so I can pass it on.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
~Nae<br>
